        </simpletable>
      </body>
    </topic>
    <topic id="topic38" xml:lang="en">
      <title id="kh155054">Automatic Statistics Collection Parameters</title>
      <body>
        <p>When automatic statistics collection is enabled, you can run <codeph>ANALYZE</codeph>
          automatically in the same transaction as an <codeph>INSERT</codeph>,
            <codeph>UPDATE</codeph>, <codeph>DELETE</codeph>, <codeph>COPY</codeph> or
            <codeph>CREATE TABLE...AS SELECT</codeph> statement when a certain threshold of rows is
          affected (<codeph>on_change</codeph>), or when a newly generated table has no statistics
            (<codeph>on_no_stats</codeph>). To enable this feature, set the following server
          configuration parameters in your Greenplum master <codeph>postgresql.conf</codeph> file
          and restart Greenplum Database: </p>
        <ul>
          <li id="kh166083">
            <codeph>gp_autostats_mode</codeph>
          </li>
          <li id="kh181502">
            <codeph>log_autostats</codeph>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <note type="warning">Depending on the specific nature of your database operations, automatic
          statistics collection can have a negative performance impact. Carefully evaluate whether
          the default setting of <codeph>on_no_stats</codeph> is appropriate for your system.</note>
      </body>
    </topic>
